aa(lp269
VSo this is only once.
p270
aVWe don't know for sure if they really understand the function of the whistles.
p271
aVOkay, so here's a second toy in the water.
p272
aVThis is a scarf toy, and I'm trying to lead the dolphin
p273
aVover to the keyboard to show her
p274
aVthe visual and the acoustic signal.
p275
aVNow this dolphin, we call her "the scarf thief,"
p276
aVbecause over the years she's absconded
p277
aVwith about 12 scarves.
p278
aVIn fact, we think she has a boutique somewhere in the Bahamas.
p279
aVSo I'm reaching over. She's got the scarf on her right side.
p280
aVAnd we try to not touch the animals too much,
p281
aVwe really don't want to over-habituate them.
p282
aVAnd I'm trying to lead her back to the keyboard.
p283
aVAnd the diver there is going to activate the scarf sound
p284
aVto request the scarf.
p285
aVSo I try to give her the scarf.
p286
aVWhoop. Almost lost it.
p287
aVBut this is the moment where everything becomes possible.
p288
aVThe dolphin's at the keyboard.
p289
aVYou've got full attention.
p290
aVAnd this sometimes went on for hours.
p291
aVAnd I wanted to share this video with you
p292
aVnot to show you any big breakthroughs,
p293
aVbecause they haven't happened yet,
p294
aVbut to show you the level of intention and focus
p295
aVthat these dolphins have, and interest in the system.
