aa(lp332
VNow, how far can this kind of communication go?
p333
aVWell, CHAT is designed specifically to empower the dolphins
p334
aVto request things from us.
p335
aVIt's designed to really be two-way.
p336
aVNow, will they learn to mimic the whistles functionally?
p337
aVWe hope so and we think so.
p338
aVBut as we decode their natural sounds,
p339
aVwe're also planning to put those back into the computerized system.
p340
aVFor example, right now we can put their own signature whistles
p341
aVin the computer and request to interact with a specific dolphin.
p342
aVLikewise, we can create our own whistles,
p343
aVour own whistle names, and let the dolphins
p344
aVrequest specific divers to interact with.
p345
aa(lp346
VNow it may be that all our mobile technology
p347
aVwill actually be the same technology that helps us
p348
aVcommunicate with another species down the road.
p349
aVIn the case of a dolphin, you know, it's a species that,
p350
aVwell, they're probably close to our intelligence in many ways
p351
aVand we might not be able to admit that right now,
p352
aVbut they live in quite a different environment,
p353
aVand you still have to bridge the gap with the sensory systems.
p354
aa(lp355
VI mean, imagine what it would be like
p356
aVto really understand the mind
p357
aVof another intelligent species on the planet.
